%N A394010 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1 - (S(p)/(S(p)+1))^2), where S(p) = Sum_{k>=0} 1/p^(2^k).
%C A394010 The asymptotic probability that two exponentially 2^n-numbers (A138302) selected independently at random are coprime.
%F A394010 Equals A394009 / A271727^2.
%e A394010 0.658118625553100445056678107891164138843144189628055...
%o A394010 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat(1 - (sum(k = 0, m, 1/p^(2^k))/(sum(k = 0, m, 1/p^(2^k)) + 1))^2);
%o A394010 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A394010 Cf. A138302, A271727, A394003, A394007, A394009.
%K A394010 nonn,cons
%O A394010 0,1
